text: Musotima ochropteralis is a moth of the family Crambidae. It was described by Achille Guenée in 1854 and is known from all of Australia. Adults are brown with various markings, including a prominent white comma-shaped spot outlined in black on each forewing. The larvae feed on Adiantum aethiopicum. ==References== Category:Musotiminae Category:Moths described in 1854
title: Musotima ochropteralis
